~ Forbidden under Penalty of Death by Beheading ~ 

- Treason against the Jarl by plan or action
- Any attack upon the Everwatch Knights
- Murder

~ Forbidden under Penalty of Death by Burning ~

- Membership in a forbidden cult 
- Practicing druidism or demonolatry
- Practicing dark necromancy
- Arson

~ Thievery ~

- Thieves and robbers shall be fined ten times the value of the stolen items, imprisoned for up to three years, and their right hand cut off
- Dealers in stolen goods or other illegal materials shall be fined five times the value of the items, imprisoned for up to two years, and branded upon the right hand
- Those who fail to pay their taxes to the Jarl shall be deemed to have stolen from His Lordship; such persons shall have their property confiscated and be imprisoned for up to one year

~ Other Criminal Acts ~

The following may lead to interrogation, fines and/or imprisonment: 
- Treasonous talk or action or support of traitors, or failure to report same
- Insulting the dignity of the Jarl or a member of the Court
- Interfering with an investigation of the Guard or the Knights
- Impersonating a Guard, Knight or Noble
- Witchcraft, human sacrifice or dangerous use of magic
- Assault or any other act of violence
- Disturbing the peace or causing a panic
- Bribery of public officials
- Possession of false documents
- Extortion

~ Command to Appear~

The Jarl may at any time command any person of Ostland to attend him at his court in Ostdor. Failure to comply may result in fine, arrest or imprisonment at his Lordship's sole discretion.
